<body>
    <div class="roadmap">
        <h1>Advanced Data Structures and Algorithms</h1>
        <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="checkpoint">Unit 1</div>
            <div class="details">
                <h2>Foundations of Data Structures and Algorithms</h2>
                <p><strong>Lecture Hours:</strong> 9</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review of Basic Data Structures (Arrays, Linked Lists, Stacks, Queues)</li>
                    <li>Complexity Analysis: Big-O, Ω, Θ Notation</li>
                    <li>Sorting Algorithms: Bubble Sort, Quick Sort, Merge Sort</li>
                    <li>Recursion and Backtracking</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="checkpoint">Unit 2</div>
            <div class="details">
                <h2>Advanced Data Structures</h2>
                <p><strong>Lecture Hours:</strong> 10</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Hashing Techniques and Hash Tables</li>
                    <li>Heaps and Priority Queues, Fibonacci Heap Sort</li>
                    <li>Binary Search Trees, AVL Trees, Red-Black Trees</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="checkpoint">Unit 3</div>
            <div class="details">
                <h2>Graph Algorithms</h2>
                <p><strong>Lecture Hours:</strong> 10</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Representation of Graphs (Adjacency Matrix/List)</li>
                    <li>BFS and DFS</li>
                    <li>Minimum Spanning Trees (Prim's, Kruskal's)</li>
                    <li>Shortest Path Algorithms (Dijkstra, Bellman-Ford, Floyd-Warshall)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="checkpoint">Unit 4</div>
            <div class="details">
                <h2>Greedy Algorithms and Dynamic Programming</h2>
                <p><strong>Lecture Hours:</strong> 12</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Greedy Strategy: Principles and Applications</li>
                    <li>Classic Problems: Huffman Encoding, Job Sequencing</li>
                    <li>Dynamic Programming: Principles and Patterns</li>
                    <li>Classic Problems: Knapsack, Matrix Chain Multiplication</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="roadmap-item">
            <div class="checkpoint">Unit 5</div>
            <div class="details">
                <h2>Advanced Topics</h2>
                <p><strong>Lecture Hours:</strong> 5</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Introduction to Randomized Algorithms</li>
                    <li>NP-Completeness and Reductions</li>
                    <li>Approximation Algorithms</li>
                    <li>Gradient Descent (ML)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
